      </row>
      <row>
        <id>20</id>
        <qid>5012</qid>
        <question>Unsafe to answer</question>
        <help />
        <script />
        <language>en</language>
      </row>
      <row>
        <id>21</id>
        <qid>232</qid>
        <question>How long has the organisation or collective been active?</question>
        <help>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Help:&lt;/strong&gt; Funders may read organisational age as a maturity signal. This assessment reads age alongside evidence, relationships and context.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; Newer groups can still be fundable when proof, trust and route fit are strong.&lt;/p&gt;</help>
        <script />
        <language>en</language>
      </row>
      <row>
        <id>22</id>
        <qid>233</qid>
        <question>What is the current registration or legal status?</question>
        <help>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Help:&lt;/strong&gt; Legal status affects eligibility, due diligence, and whether a direct, fiscal-host, intermediary, or partner route is safest.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; Use the safest accurate answer. If exact details create risk, use an approximate answer or choose Not applicable / Unsafe to answer.&lt;/p&gt;</help>
        <script />
        <language>en</language>
      </row>
      <row>
        <id>23</id>
        <qid>234</qid>
        <question>Do the legal, banking, proposal, public, and partner names match closely enough for funder verification?</question>
        <help>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Help:&lt;/strong&gt; Name mismatches can slow or block due diligence. Think about proposal names, bank account names, registration documents, public platforms, and partner records.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; Use the safest accurate answer. If exact details create risk, use an approximate answer or choose Not applicable / Unsafe to answer.&lt;/p&gt;</help>
        <script />
        <language>en</language>
      </row>
      <row>
        <id>24</id>
        <qid>235</qid>
        <question>How can the organisation currently receive grant funds? Select all that apply.</question>
        <help>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Help:&lt;/strong&gt; Many CSOs have more than one possible receiving route. Select all routes that are currently realistic and safe.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; Use the safest accurate answer. If exact details create risk, use an approximate answer or choose Not applicable / Unsafe to answer.&lt;/p&gt;</help>
        <script />
        <language>en</language>
      </row>
      <row>
        <id>25</id>
        <qid>5013</qid>
        <question>Own organisational bank account</question>
        <help />
        <script />
        <language>en</language>
      </row>
      <row>
        <id>26</id>
        <qid>5014</qid>
        <question>Fiscal host</question>
        <help />
        <script />
        <language>en</language>
      </row>
      <row>
        <id>27</id>
        <qid>5015</qid>
        <question>Partner or intermediary receives funds</question>
        <help />
