        <language>en</language>
      </row>
      <row>
        <id>383</id>
        <qid>5211</qid>
        <question>Not applicable / Unsafe to answer</question>
        <help />
        <script />
        <language>en</language>
      </row>
      <row>
        <id>418</id>
        <qid>5246</qid>
        <question>Which funding routes should be used, repaired, delayed, or avoided before the next ask?</question>
        <help>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Help:&lt;/strong&gt; A route is the practical path into funding, not just the funder name. Choose the current status of each route so the report can recommend where to put effort next.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; A cold open call may be possible but low-fit. A fiscal host route may be stronger if direct receipt is not yet safe or traceable. A warm referral may be the best next move if trust already exists.&lt;/p&gt;</help>
        <script />
        <language>en</language>
      </row>
      <row>
        <id>419</id>
        <qid>5247</qid>
        <question>Warm referral or trusted introduction</question>
        <help />
        <script />
        <language>en</language>
      </row>
      <row>
        <id>420</id>
        <qid>5248</qid>
        <question>Past funder repeat or renewal conversation</question>
        <help />
        <script />
        <language>en</language>
      </row>
